career resources arts at stanford university presented by sica home search this site arts enews subscribe for students career resources launching careers in the arts sometimes require a certain measure of resourcefulness and creativity but don t despair there are a number of resources online on campus and in the bay area that can help start you on a path toward a career in the arts and provide advice and guidance keep in mind that professors in arts departments are an extremely valuable resource and are more than likely happy to help you explore your interests in the arts and identify opportunities accordingly sica sica offers a number of opportunities to wet your feet in arts administration academic year internships in the sica office include student arts social media photography and videography positions sica's summer internship program places students with arts organizations in san francisco and the bay area new york city and other locations with a paid stipend for more information on these opportunities to explore and begin careers in the arts visit the here for more information alumni network and mentoring the stanford alumni mentoring program sam through the cdc offers the opportunity for stanford students to connect with an alum and build a one on one mentoring relationship for career guidance advice and advocacy for more information visit mentoring stanford edu email lists to be on the weekly artsupdate includes a section devoted to arts opportunities and events on and off campus subscribe here the cdc's arts media communication newsletter includes jobs and internships in the arts as well as events and other resources for information on how to subscrible click here listings for jobs internships fellowships in the arts americans for the arts new york foundation for the arts idealist artsearch creative hotlist artjob center for arts management and technology at carnegie mellon arts opportunities prospective students check out the arts guide your multimedia gui